  "prompt": "How much importance should be given to patents before you build your idea?",
  "response": "The importance of patents depends on several factors:\n\n1. Industry-specific considerations:\n- Tech/pharma: High patent importance\n- Service/creative industries: Lower patent importance\n- Manufacturing: Moderate to high importance\n\n2. Patent value assessment:\n- Uniqueness of your idea\n- Potential market size\n- Commercial viability\n- Cost of patent filing\n- Competitive landscape\n\n3. Strategic approaches:\n- Provisional patents for initial protection\n- Full patent if technology is groundbreaking\n- Trade secret alternative\n- Non-disclosure agreements (NDAs)\n\n4. When to prioritize patents:\n- Before public disclosure\n- When idea has clear commercial potential\n- If technology is easily copyable\n- If funding/investors require protection\n\n5. Cost considerations:\n- Patent filing can be expensive ($5,000-$15,000)\n- Ongoing maintenance costs\n- International patent protection increases expense\n\n6. Alternatives to consider:\n- First-mover advantage\n- Rapid innovation/iteration\n- Strong execution\n- Building brand/network\n\n7. Recommendation:\n- Consult IP lawyer\n- Do thorough market research\n- Assess individual idea's unique characteristics\n\nBalanced approach: Protect truly innovative aspects without overinvesting.",
